title: Asian stocks subdued ahead of this week's trade talks
text: Asian markets were subdued in early trading Monday, as important parts of the region were closed for public holidays.

title: Oil prices slip again amid gathering gloom over global economy
text: Oil prices fell on Monday, extending last week's heavy losses, with traders fearing the global economic slowdown will weigh on future oil demand growth while pegging hopes for a rebound on progress in talks this week on ending the U.S.-China trade war.

title: Asian shares buoyed by U.S. jobs, trade talks in focus
text: Asian shares edged higher on Monday after data showed the U.S. unemployment rate dropped to the lowest in almost 50 years, easing concerns of a slowdown in the world's largest economy.

title: U.S. Natural Gas Reserves Continue To Soar
text: It's been a consistent theme since the U.S. shale revolution took flight in 2008: not just surging natural gas production but also surging gas reserves.

title: Low inflation? Nothing to worry about, Fed's George says
text: Kansas City Federal Reserve Bank President Esther George on Sunday rejected the notion that the U.S. central bank should  cut interest rates to try to boost low inflation, adding that doing so could create financial imbalances.

title: China takes some key trade issues off the negotiating table with U.S.: report
text: Chinese officials have significantly narrowed the scope of issues they're willing to discuss at upcoming trade negotiations with the U.S., Bloomberg News reported Sunday.

title: Look For The Preponderance Of The Evidence, Don’t Rely On One Factor

title: China is reportedly reluctant to agree to a broad US trade deal with talks set to restart

title: Can An October Rate Cut Really Help Stocks?
